ğŸ“Œ Introduction

Container images allow us to package:

Application code

Runtime

Libraries

Dependencies

into a pre-defined format.

Container runtimes such as:

runC

containerd

CRI-O

use these images to create and run containers.

While these runtimes can run containers on a single host, production environments require:

Fault tolerance

Scalability

High availability

To achieve this, we use a container orchestrator, which acts as a centralized controller managing multiple connected hosts as a cluster.

ğŸ“¦ What Are Containers?

Containers are an application-centric method to deliver:

High-performing applications

Scalable applications

Portable applications

They provide:

Isolated environments

Lightweight virtualization

No interference between applications

Containers are especially suitable for microservices architecture, where applications are split into smaller independent services.

